# ============================================
# Life-OS .gitignore
# Framework (shared) vs Instance (private)
# ============================================

# --- PRIVATE: Personal content (never syncs) ---
Days/*.md
!Days/README.md
briefings/*.md
briefings/*.html
!briefings/README.md
CLAUDE.md
CHIEF-OF-STAFF.md
STATUS.md
WEEKLY-LOG.md
PRIORITIES.md
ACCOUNTING.md
OCTOPUS.md
THE-DESCENT.md
MEMORIES.md
*.DIALOGUES.md
*.VISION*.md
*.html
NEGOTIATION-SKILLS.md
DEALCRAFT.md
BOTTLENECK.md
AGENT-BTD.md
GCH.md

# --- PRIVATE: Personal agents (instance-specific projects) ---
.claude/agents/daily-ops.md
.claude/agents/personas.md
.claude/agents/meta.md

# --- PRIVATE: Machine-specific config ---
.claude/config.local.json
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.claude/telegram/.env
.claude/telegram/state.json
.claude/telegram/queue.json
.claude/telegram/bot.log
.claude/autonomous/logs/

# --- PRIVATE: Node dependencies (reinstall per machine) ---
node_modules/
.claude/telegram/node_modules/

# --- PRIVATE: Transfer staging ---
transfer/

# --- PRIVATE: Project metadata with personal content ---
# Add your project folders here following this pattern:
# ProjectName/*.md
# !ProjectName/README.md
# This ignores personal assessment/about files while keeping template READMEs

# --- PRIVATE: Agent research ---
# agent-research/

# --- PRIVATE: OS/IDE artifacts ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
